p: \bHe gave me the same speech a while ago. It's how I was able to meet my partner.
\bListen. He's a bit... intense. I trust him though. I hope you do too.
\bBut anyways, are you ready for our battle? I'm anxious to get started!
\bMy Gym isn't just a Water-gym. I focus on Water in every possible way.
\bThe ocean, the lakes, the rivers. And yes, even the rain that fills them.
\bThe rain is one of the most important natural forces in the world.
\bIt keeps the world alive and healthy, and keeps the water cycle going.
\bBut it's also one of the most destructive- and I'm about to show you why.
\bJeez. When Diana phoned me up to tell me somebody beat her, I had no idea you were THAT good.
\bYou really are fantastic. You'll be a great addition to our group.
\bThis will let higher level Pokemon obey you.
\bAnd just cause I like ya so much, have this, too.
\bThat TM contains the move Calm Mind.
\bI know, it's a bit odd for a Rain leader to give out a Psychic TM.
\bI promise you though- it's a fantastic move. It's definitely worth having!
\bNow... since the First Augur disappeared, we don't actually have an eighth Gym Leader for you to face.
\bIn the meantime though, I guess y-
???: \bAttention, please! Your attention, please! Broadcast starting in two minutes!
\bUh... I'll be right back? What on earth...
\rYou'll never get to Calreath! You'll lose right here!
pbTrainerBattle(PBTrainers::SWIMMER_F,"Karen",_I("I wish I could catch them all!"),false,0)
\bI wish I could catch them all!
\rI love battling in the water! It's so much fun!
\rYou're not going anywhere! Get set to get decked!
\bThe Leader here, Calreath, runs a Rain-themed Gym.
\bNicely done, champ, I can't believe you beat Calreath!
